      <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
         <head>Biographical History</head>
         
      <p>Arthur L. Carson (1895- ) was a graduate of Cornell University and president of Silliman University in the Philippines from 1939 to 1953.  He was also the first president of Trinity College of Quezon City (later Trinity University of Asia).</p></bioghist>
      
